#Approach:

Sort Characters By Frequency – HashMap + Bucket Sort Approach

Is problem me hume string ke characters ko unki frequency ke decreasing order me arrange karna hota hai.

Sabse pehle ek HashMap use karke har character ki frequency count karte hain.

Uske baad maximum frequency nikalte hain.
Ab hum bucket sort ka idea use karte hain.
Ek buckets array banate hain jahan index frequency ko represent karta hai.
Matlab jis character ki frequency 3 hai, usse buckets[3] me store kar denge.

Phir high frequency se low frequency tak buckets traverse karte hain.
Jis bucket me characters milte hain, un characters ko unki frequency ke according answer string me add kar dete hain.

Isse jo character sabse zyada baar aata hai wo pehle aayega,
phir usse kam frequency wale characters aayenge.

Important:
Agar do characters ki frequency same ho, to unka relative order matter nahi karta.
Bas same character ko ek saath group me add karna hota hai.

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(n)

#Code:

class Solution {
    public String frequencySort(String s) {
        if(s.length() == 0) return "";

        HashMap<Character, Integer> map = new HashMap<>();
        for(int i=0; i<s.length(); i++){
            map.put(s.charAt(i), map.getOrDefault(s.charAt(i), 0)+1);
        }

        int maxFreq = Collections.max(map.values());
        List<Character>[] buckets = new List[maxFreq + 1];

        // Fill buckets
        for (char key : map.keySet()) {
            int freq = map.get(key);
            if (buckets[freq] == null) {
                buckets[freq] = new ArrayList<>();
            }
            buckets[freq].add(key);
        }

        StringBuilder ans = new StringBuilder();

        for (int i = maxFreq; i >= 1; i--) {
            if (buckets[i] != null) {
                for (char ch : buckets[i]) {
                    for (int j = 0; j < i; j++) {
                        ans.append(ch);
                    }
                }
            }
        }

        return ans.toString();
    }
}
